ontal.coordinate_system_details"}, {"values": ["12.5 km "], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.grid.discretisation.horizontal.horizontal_resolution"}, {"values": ["480 x 480. This includes the relaxation zone and the bi-periodization zone (11 points)", "In the spectral space, truncation order for linear grid in x and in y: 239"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.grid.discretisation.horizontal.full_domain"}, {"values": ["8 points, Davies (1976) type relaxation"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.grid.discretisation.horizontal.relaxation_zone"}, {"values": ["453 x 453"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.grid.discretisation.horizontal.inner_domain"}, {"values": ["spectral", "fixed grid"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.grid.discretisation.horizontal.scheme_type"}, {"values": ["Other: spectral"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.grid.discretisation.horizontal.scheme_order"}, {"values": ["Other: not needed"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.grid.discretisation.horizontal.horizontal_pole"}, {"values": ["Latitude-Longitude"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.grid.discretisation.horizontal.grid_type"}]}, {"meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicPropertySet"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.grid.discretisation.vertical", "properties": [{"values": ["hybrid sigma-pressure: sigma system near terrain and isobaric above"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.grid.discretisation.vertical.coordinate_type"}]}], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.Topic"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.grid.discretisation"}]}, "keyProperties": {"meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.Topic"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties", "properties": [{"values": ["CNRM-ALADIN in its climate version 6.3 (CNRM-ALADIN63)"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.name"}, {"values": ["ALADIN, CNRM, France, Toulouse, ARPEGE-Climat, CORDEX, Euro-CORDEX, Med-CORDEX, "], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.keywords"}, {"values": ["CNRM-ALADIN63 is the version 6.3 of the ALADIN Regional Climate Model in use at CNRM (M\u00e9t\u00e9o-France, CNRS, Universit\u00e9 de Toulouse, Toulouse, France). It is described in Nabat et al. (2020, https://doi.org/10.5194/acp-20-8315-2020). The CNRM-ALADIN63 RCM includes an atmospheric component (also called CNRM-ALADIN63) RCM and the SURFEX platform (Decharme et al. 2019) to represent the land surfaces. The atmospheric component, CNRM-ALADIN63, is based on the cycle 37 of the ARPEGE/IFS model (declared in 2010), developed under a collaboration between M\u00e9t\u00e9o-France, ECMWF and the ALADIN consortium. CNRM-ALADIN63 can be considered as the nearly perfect limited area version of the GCM ARPEGE-Climat Version 6.3 used as the atmospheric component of the CNRM Global Climate and Earth System models in CMIP6 (CNRM-CM6-1 and CNRM-ESM2-1) as it shares most of its physics and dynamics with it. In comparison to CNRM-ALADIN52 and CNRM-ALADIN53 used previously in CORDEX over different domains, most of the atmospheric physics has been updated or revisited (Roehrig et al. 2019, Voldoire et al. 2019, Nabat et al. 2020). The model has an hydrostatic dynamical core, an hybrid sigma-pressure vertical coordinate system and a Lambert conformal conic projection for the horizontal grid spacing. For the Euro-CORDEX configuration, CNRM-ALADIN63 uses 91 vertical levels and a 12.5km horizontal grid. More information: https://www.umr-cnrm.fr/spip.php?article125&lang=en "], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.overview"}, {"values": ["ARCM: Atmospheric Regional Climate Model"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.model_family"}, {"values": ["hydrostatic", "Boussinesq", "Primitive equations"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.basic_approximations"}], "subTopics": [{"meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.Topic"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.resolution", "properties": [{"values": ["12.5 x 12.5 km (roughly 0.11x0.11 degrees)"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.resolution.canonical_horizontal_resolution"}, {"values": ["91.0"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.resolution.number_of_vertical_levels"}, {"values": ["True"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.resolution.high_top"}]}, {"meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.Topic"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.timestepping", "properties": [{"values": ["450.0"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.timestepping.timestep_dynamics"}, {"values": ["3600.0"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.timestepping.timestep_shortwave_radiative_transfer"}, {"values": ["3600.0"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.timestepping.timestep_longwave_radiative_transfer"}]}, {"meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.Topic"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.orography", "properties": [{"values": ["fixed: present day"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.orography.type"}]}, {"meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.Topic"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.tuning_applied", "properties": [{"values": ["By choice, CNRM-ALADIN63 has been kept as close as possible of its GCM ARPEGE-Climate Version 6.3 counterpart used in CMIP6 with limited adaptations due to higher spatial resolution (12.5 km instead of 150 km) in order to create a nearly perfect GCM/RCM pair. Therefore no specific tuning has been done for the RCM: a significant part of the parameterization internal parameters, especially for the moist physics, were first guessed using single-column simulations of a few case studies (mostly shallow and deep convection). Then other relevant parameters (especially those regarding cloud microphysics and cloud radiative properties) were further tuned regarding global targets (see cmip6_cnrm-cerfacs_cnrm-cm6-1_atmos.xlsx)."], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.tuning_applied.description"}, {"values": ["no specific tuning for CNRM-ALADIN63 (see cmip6_cnrm-cerfacs_cnrm-cm6-1_atmos.xlsx for the tuning of the GCM version)."], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.tuning_applied.regional_metrics_used"}, {"values": ["None"], "meta": {"type": "cim.2.science.TopicProperty"}, "specializationID": "cordex.atmos.key_properties.tuning_applied.trend_metrics_used"}]}]}}], "canonicalID": "cnrm-aladin63", "modelType": "RCM", "name": "CNRM-ALADIN63"}